# Cursor Rules for Spaniel Salon App

## TypeScript Naming Conventions

- TypeScript variables should use camelCase naming convention
- TypeScript variables should NOT start with an underscore (_)
- Private variables should use camelCase (e.g., `darkModeSignal`, not `_darkModeSignal`)
- Public variables should use camelCase
- Maintain consistency with existing codebase variable names when refactoring
